			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When WTD pet is summoned, it immediately aggro's whatever mob is targetted.  You cannot give the pet anything while it is thus engaged.  When the target dies, the wtd pet will only swing at anything that swings or casts on you.  That means that (a) you have to give a powerful item to a pet that will exist for less than 90 seconds and (b) you have to get hit by "uber_mob_01" which is more likely than not to kill you if it's really that powerful.
<br />

<br />
That being said, you COULD give your summoned pet a weapon that procs slow or whatnot...it would still vanish as soon as the pet dies and you would still have no chance to get it back...I would never do it.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~topknot/wsb/media/350795/site1015.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
Arch Lich <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592061" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sthythys Sthythophilous</a>
<br />
The Lizardly Lich of <a href="http://www.savagearms.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Savage Arms</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
